Job Description:
The team works to minimise the damage of inauthentic behaviours on various platforms, covering multiple classical and novel community and business risk areas such as account integrity, engagement authenticity, anti spam, API abuse, growth fraud, live streaming security, and financial safety (ads or e-commerce), etc.

Responsibilities
Follow up with standard process to respond to reported risk cases in a timely and accurate manner via internal platforms and support tools;
Summarize and classify the feedback cases reported, check the response and case solving quality weekly.
Figure out the shorteness or issues of online risk control policy and process while handling cases, work with internal team to improve the policy and process.
Educate internal and external stakeholders to ensure compliance with our processes;
Qualifications
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to influence and reach agreements with others;
Ability to maintain composure in critical situations and communicate clearly with both internal and external stakeholders;
Details oriented, self-driven and curious to learn and work independently in a fast-paced environment.

